## 🔒 3. Security & Compliance

**"You're sending bank data to an external LLM — isn't that a security risk?"**
> This is a great question and a common concern. The LLM only receives the **taxonomy JSON and Excel spec** — both of which are provided by the regulator and contain **zero actual bank data**. Real financial figures only enter the picture in Layer 4 (Java), which runs entirely on Citi's internal infrastructure.

**"What if the regulator changes the taxonomy — how quickly can you adapt?"**
> That's exactly the problem we solve. Today it takes 2–4 weeks. With our engine, you re-run the Python extractors on the new taxonomy ZIP and Excel spec, feed the updated JSONs to the LLM, and get a new template in under 2 hours — zero code changes.

**"Has this been validated against real production submissions?"**
> Yes. We validated against R396 (100% fact match, 284 facts) and R322 (89.1% match, 763 out of 856 facts). These are real reports that Citi has already submitted to RBI in production.

