## 🛠️ 5. Technical Feasibility

**"How long would it take to go from this PoC to full production?"**
> The roadmap has 6 phases across 12 weeks. Phase 0 (architecture) is already complete. The PoC (R419) is the hackathon demo. Full production with CLI tool and new report onboarding in under 2 hours is Phase 5.

**"Why Python? Citi's existing system is Java — won't there be integration issues?"**
> The Python engine outputs an XML file. That XML file is consumed by the existing Java XMLConverter exactly as before — no integration change needed. Python and Java are completely decoupled. Python was chosen because it's 3x faster to develop with for this kind of extraction and LLM integration work.

**"What is the bus factor of this new system — are you creating a new dependency?"**
> The old system had a bus factor of 2–3 specialized Java developers. Our engine eliminates that — anyone with the taxonomy ZIP and Excel spec can generate a template. The system itself is documented, open to any LLM, and the prompts are a reusable library.

