## ⚠️ 7. Tough / Skeptical Questions

**"89.1% accuracy on R322 is not 100% — is that good enough for regulatory filing?"**
> For a PoC, 89.1% on a 856-fact report is strong. The self-correction loop is designed to close that gap. R396 already hits 100%. The target for production is ≥95% with zero manual intervention, and the remaining edge cases are being analyzed to improve the prompts.

**"What prevents a competitor from building the same thing in 3 months?"**
> Three things — deep Citi domain knowledge of RBI taxonomy quirks that generic tools miss, 3 already-validated production reports as training/benchmark data, and the existing Java XMLConverter framework that took years to build. A competitor starts from scratch on all three.

**"What if regulators change the Excel spec format entirely and hidden cells are no longer used?"**
> The Python extractors (Layer 2) are the only part that would need updating — and that's just one layer out of four. The LLM engine, Java converter, and validation layers are completely unaffected. Updating one extractor is far cheaper than rewriting report-specific Java code.

